                <h2>Nutritional Needs for Ducks</h2>
                <p>Providing a balanced diet is key to maintaining duck health:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Waterfowl Feed:</strong> Specialized feed for ducks provides necessary nutrients. Ensure feed is fresh and free from contaminants.</li>
                    <li><strong>Vegetables:</strong> Ducks enjoy a variety of vegetables, including leafy greens, corn, and peas.</li>
                    <li><strong>Grains:</strong> Offer grains such as wheat and barley as part of their diet to provide energy.</li>
                    <li><strong>Water:</strong> Provide constant access to clean water for drinking and foraging.</li>
                </ul>
                <p>Avoid feeding ducks bread or processed foods. Consult a poultry nutritionist for tailored dietary plans.</p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Environmental Needs -->
        <section class="info-section">
            <div class="info-container">
                <h2>Ideal Environment for Ducks</h2>
                <p>A suitable living environment supports duck health and well-being:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Housing:</strong> Provide a dry, draft-free shelter with adequate space for ducks to move around comfortably.</li>
                    <li><strong>Water Source:</strong> Ducks need access to a pond, pool, or similar water source for swimming and cleaning.</li>
                    <li><strong>Temperature:</strong> Ensure the housing is protected from extreme temperatures and provides proper ventilation.</li>
                </ul>
                <p>Regularly clean the living area to prevent disease and ensure proper hygiene.</p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Common Diseases and Prevention -->
        <section class="info-section">
            <div class="info-container">
                <h2>Health Challenges and Disease Prevention</h2>
                <p>Preventing common health issues in ducks is crucial for their well-being:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Duck Viral Enteritis:</strong> Monitor for symptoms like lethargy and diarrhea. Maintain good hygiene and biosecurity practices.</li>
                    <li><strong>Parasites:</strong> Regularly check for external and internal parasites. Consult a vet for appropriate treatments.</li>
                    <li><strong>Foot Problems:</strong> Ensure clean and dry bedding to prevent foot infections and injuries.</li>
                </ul>
                <p>Regular veterinary check-ups and vaccination programs are essential for disease prevention.</p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Health Maintenance and Best Practices -->
